{hello 2023} 🌿 as I enter this new year, my first {full} year of motherhood, it’s going to be a year of so many firsts: first smiles, first laughs, first play dates + new friends, first holidays + celebrations, and so much more. I’m looking forward to embracing it all 🤍 but alongside those happy times, I know it won’t be without hardship + challenges. 
⁣
As we took one of our first {albeit, very slowww} family walks through our favorite park New Year’s Day, I was thinking how *wild* it is how quickly perspective + priorities shift. All thanks to our tiniest addition. He’s the absolute joy of my life, and I find he’s already changing me for the better. My hope for myself this year, is I continue learning to…⁣
⁣
• embrace the unknown ⁣
• lean into the growing pains ⁣
• celebrate the slow moments ⁣
⁣
…all while giving myself grace to stumble + sometimes fail. 2023 is bound to be my favorite yet 💛 #happynewyear #freshperspective #newmama

12 Tips for Traveling w. a Newborn ✈️ We booked a family vacation w. our 9 week old to Mexico. Here’s what we learned along the way:⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
1. Wear baby through security + boarding.⁣
⁣
2. Feed during takeoff + landing; helps w. their ears. Although don’t wake to feed. We found he was totally fine if already asleep, so waited until scheduled feed times to wake + feed to keep the routine as close to at home as possible.⁣
⁣
3. You CAN bring breast milk + distilled water through security; just tell them it’s for formula.⁣
⁣
4. Bring more diapers + wipes than you think you might need. Also consider using overnight diapers.⁣
⁣
5. Extra change of clothes or top for mom + dad.⁣
⁣
6. Bring 2 changes of clothes for baby.⁣
⁣
7. Disposable puppy pads to lay down + toss for diaper changes.⁣
⁣
8. Zip lock bags or doggie poop bags for wet clothes + dirty diapers.⁣
⁣
9. You can’t beat the white noise on an airport for sleep, but bring a travel/portable white noise machine for going through the airport.⁣
⁣
10. Invest in a Doona; the 2-in-1 infant car seat/stroller is worth every penny. You can gate check, so you can push baby in it during a layover and/or all the way to the gate if you don’t wear in a carrier. And then use for in-car transportation once you land.⁣
⁣
11. Ask your gate agent if it’s a full flight. If not, see if they’re able to shift any sets around to ensure an empty seat in your row. We also booked an isle + window to help w. this probability ahead of time!⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
12. Most importantly stay positive, flexible + patient! Not everything will go perfectly, but that’s ok. You’re prepared. You can do this. On our first trip we had a few hiccups…I didn’t realize my pre-check had expired, so longer security for us, we left my husband’s phone on the plane (was recovered), and Clarke peed through his diaper all over mom about 30 minutes before landing at our final destination 🤪 Not the worst! Remember it’s just ONE day, and you’ll get back on track the following.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ You’re doing it for the memories!⁣
⁣
ANY OTHER SUGGESTIONS!? Leave in comments so other families can take note 💛 #travelingwithbaby #flyingwithbaby #newborntravel #EXPLOREbyK

Last summer while visiting Nantucket, a friend and I came across *the* most incredible coconut chia pudding. I’m talking stop you mind bite, ‘you’ve got to try this’ chia pudding. Needless to say, she set out to recreate the recipe + it’s become one of my go-to summer snacks ever since! Smelling @yankeecandle’s Coconut Beach fragrance instantly took me back to that first bite, and I knew it was something I wanted (no, needed!) to share w. y’all! #ad⁣
⁣
EASIEST COCONUT CHIA PUDDING:⁣
• 2 cans coconut milk (I’ve tried several brands, but think Whole Foods 365 is the best)⁣
• 1/2 cup chia seeds (add more/less based on your preferred consistency)⁣
• 3-5 dashes of vanilla extract ⁣
• Swirl of maple syrup ⁣
• Separate liquid into individual sized containers + chill for at least a couple hours (I prefer overnight)⁣
• Garnish w. toasted coconut flakes, slivered almond + fresh berries or fruit of your choice⁣
⁣
#YCAmbassador #chiapudding #summersnack #ENTERTAINbyK

A mini Christmas recap ❤️🎄 Clarke’s second Christmas almost felt like his first since last year he was 17 days old and we were still in that newborn fog. But still kept the day low key, which was perfect. Went on a family walk in the morning before the rain to take in the fresh air + festive entries - I’ll never tire of them! Had Sterling’s family over for a feast of a brunch (which included Sterling’s first try at homemade buttermilk biscuits 🤤), ornamented w. some of my favorite antique finds I’ve collected over the years (hello hand painted French egg cups). Followed by FaceTime Christmas + gift exchange w. my family in Colorado. Missed celebrating alongside them this year, but didn’t miss the hectic travel! ⁣
⁣
Capped the night off back in matching @dear.georgie pjs for our little family of 3 Christmas w. stockings. Along w. Clarke’s current favorite snack @amarababyfood 😂 truly obsessed. Leftover Indian takeout for mom + dad. ⁣
⁣
Merry Christmas, y’all!!!
